issues.title: Active Suspension System Failure
issues.description: The active suspension system experiences failures in the hydraulic components, causing the vehicle to drop to minimum ride height and become undrivable. This affects the Proactive Chassis Control II system.
symptoms: Vehicle suddenly drops to lowest ride height
issues.fix_description: Replace hydraulic suspension components, recalibrate system, update software
issues.prevention: Regular suspension system inspections, avoid harsh impacts, keep system software updated

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly the front splitter and rear wing, experience delamination where the carbon fiber layers separate, affecting structural integrity and appearance.
symptoms: Visible separation of carbon fiber layers
White or cloudy areas on carbon panels
issues.fix_description: Replace affected carbon fiber panels, apply proper adhesives, refinish surface
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, protect from UV exposure, regular inspection of panels

issues.title: Infotainment System Software Glitches
issues.description: The IRIS infotainment system experiences frequent software crashes, freezing, and connectivity issues with smartphones and navigation functions.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, system reset, potential hardware replacement if needed
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid using incompatible devices, regular system resets

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The electronic door handle mechanisms fail to operate properly, preventing doors from opening or closing correctly. This affects both driver and passenger doors.
symptoms: Doors won't open with button press
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle actuators, recalibrate electronic systems, lubricate mechanisms
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of door mechanisms, avoid forcing doors, keep electronic systems clean

issues.title: Brake System Overheating
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brakes experience overheating during track use, leading to brake fade and potential damage to brake components despite being designed for high-performance use.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and potentially discs, upgrade brake cooling, adjust brake system settings
issues.prevention: Allow proper cool-down periods during track use, use appropriate brake fluid, regular brake inspections

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: The 4.0L twin-turbo V8 engine shows higher than normal oil consumption, requiring frequent top-ups between service intervals.
issues.fix_description: Inspect engine seals, replace worn components, check PCV system, potential engine rebuild in severe cases
issues.prevention: Use recommended oil grade, regular oil changes, monitor oil levels frequently, avoid overrevving when cold

issues.title: Transmission Shift Quality Issues
issues.description: The 7-speed dual-clutch transmission experiences harsh shifting, delayed engagement, or failure to shift properly, particularly in track mode.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software updates, clutch replacement, transmission fluid service, potential transmission rebuild
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, proper warm-up procedures, avoid aggressive shifts when cold

issues.title: Cooling System Leaks
issues.description: Coolant leaks develop in various parts of the cooling system, including radiators, hoses, and water pumps, potentially leading to engine overheating.
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking components, pressure test cooling system, flush and refill coolant
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system inspections, use proper coolant mix, avoid overheating, replace coolant as scheduled

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System Malfunction
issues.description: TPMS sensors frequently malfunction or provide inaccurate readings, leading to false warnings or inability to monitor tire pressures properly.
issues.fix_description: Replace TPMS sensors, reprogram system, check sensor batteries
issues.prevention: Careful tire installation, avoid damage to sensors, regular system checks

issues.title: Electrical System Intermittent Failures
issues.description: Various electrical components experience intermittent failures, including lighting systems, electronic controls, and auxiliary systems.
symptoms: Intermittent loss of power to accessories
issues.fix_description: Diagnose electrical system, replace faulty components, check wiring harnesses, update software
issues.prevention: Keep electrical connections clean, avoid water exposure, regular electrical system checks

editorial.tagline: Track-bred predator disguised as road car
editorial.hero_blurb: The 765LT represents McLaren's most focused road-going weapon, blending savage track performance with surprising daily usability. This is what happens when Woking's finest engineers are given free rein to create the ultimate driver's machine.
editorial.essence: McLaren's most uncompromising road car, the 765LT strips away comfort in favor of pure speed and connection. Every component exists solely to make you faster, from the carbon fiber seats to the active aerodynamics that generate genuine downforce at highway speeds.
editorial.heritage: Born from McLaren's 'Longtail' philosophy first seen in the legendary F1 GTR, the 765LT carries forward the tradition of extreme aerodynamic optimization and weight reduction that made McLaren a dominant force in motorsport.
editorial.design_philosophy: Form follows function taken to its logical extreme - every curve, vent, and wing serves aerodynamic or cooling purposes, creating a purposeful aesthetic that prioritizes performance over mere beauty.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the 765LT itself doesn't race, it inherits DNA from McLaren's championship-winning Formula 1 program and successful GT racing efforts, translating decades of motorsport knowledge into road-legal form.
editorial.engine_character: The 4.0L twin-turbo V8 delivers explosive power with virtually no lag, feeling more like a naturally aspirated engine with supernatural torque multiplication across the entire rev range.
editorial.transmission_feel: The seven-speed dual-clutch shifts with pneumatic precision, offering telepathic responses in Track mode while remaining surprisingly smooth in comfort settings.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Suspension that reads the road like poetry, maintaining perfect composure through direction changes while providing enough compliance to tackle real-world surfaces without breaking your spine.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically-assisted precision that communicates every detail of the road surface while requiring genuine effort at parking speeds - old-school feedback in a modern package.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon-ceramic stoppers that inspire absolute confidence, with a firm pedal feel and fade-free performance that matches the car's incredible straight-line capability.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated symphony of turbo whistle, wastegate chatter, and crackling overrun that builds to a purposeful roar under full acceleration without becoming obnoxious.
editorial.ideal_owner: Serious driving enthusiasts who prioritize track capability and pure performance over comfort, status, or practicality considerations.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking luxury, comfort, practicality, or those intimidated by a car that demands respect and skill to fully exploit safely.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 765LT represents the pinnacle of McLaren's road car engineering, offering genuine supercar performance with surprising usability. Buy one if you want the closest thing to a street-legal race car that major manufacturers produce.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
